openVideoDevice

public void openVideoDevice(long nGroupID,
                            long nUserID,
                            java.lang.String szDeviceID,
                            v2av.VideoPlayer vp,
                            int businessType)
Request to open video device include remote user and self.

Parameters:
nGroupID - conference id. If open P2P user device, this parameter should be 0
nUserID - user id
szDeviceID - user device ID. If open local user camera device, user ""
vp - if open local device, input null. Otherwise VideoPlayer
businessType - 1 : conference 2: IM type
See Also:
#OnRemoteUserVideoDevice(String)}, VideoPlayer, V2ClientType.CONF, V2ClientType.IM

closeVideoDevice

public void closeVideoDevice(long nGroupID,
                             long nUserID,
                             java.lang.String szDeviceID,
                             v2av.VideoPlayer vp,
                             int businessType)
Request to close video device. This function no callback call

Parameters:
nGroupID - conference id. If open P2P user device, this parameter should be 0
nUserID - user id
szDeviceID - user device ID. If open local user camera device, user ""
vp - if open local device, input null. Otherwise input VideoPlayer
businessType - 1: conference 2: IM type
See Also:
#OnRemoteUserVideoDevice(String)}, VideoPlayer, V2ClientType.CONF, V2ClientType.IM

setCapParam

public void setCapParam(java.lang.String szDevID,
                        int nSizeIndex,
                        int nFrameRate,
                        int nBitRate)
    Update local camera configuration. JNI call OnSetCapParamDone(String, int, int, int) to indicate response.

Parameters:
szDevID - ""
nSizeIndex - it's camera index
nFrameRate - 15
nBitRate - 256000
